-- OGX Raised to `Buy' From `Hold' at Citigroup on 2011 Crude Oil Outlook
-- Alexander Cuadros
-- 2010-07-26T12:06:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/ogx-raised-to-buy-from-hold-at-citigroup-on-2011-crude-oil-outlook.html

          
          
             OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA ,
the oil company controlled by Brazilian billionaire  Eike Batista , was raised to “buy” from “hold” at Citigroup Inc.  
 OGX, which trades at an “undemanding valuation,” will
benefit as oil prices are expected to rise starting in 2011,
analysts  Pedro Medeiros  and  Felipe Jiman Koh  wrote in a note to
clients dated July 23.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
